This paper deals with the classification of medical images using machine learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of feature ranking strategies and boosted decision tree and decision forest classifiers suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of computation time complexity and cloud-based analysis systems suggests a possible focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
